&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Division of Medicine and Urgent Care&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Emergency Nurse Practitioner &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 7 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now is a great time to join our team as an Emergency Nurse Practitioner in the Accident and Emergency Department at Tameside and Glossop Integrated Care NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Having just secured £16M investment for our Emergency Care Village there has never been a more exciting time to join our Urgent Care Family!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for experienced Emergency Nurse Practitioners who are committed to working as part of our Urgent Care Family to deliver an excellent, caring service to our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working as an autonomous nurse practitioner, you will have the skills to assess both adults and paediatrics with minor illness and minor injuries, formulate a clinical management plan onto discharge or transfer for definitive care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Both our patients and our staff are important to us - Everyone Matters, and so you will be valuable member of the team, supporting the department and junior staff to develop the workforce in order to deliver exceptional quality care. In return, we can offer you accesses to a dedicated Practice Based Educator and the opportunity for flexible working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants are expected to have completed University based ENP course at Level 6 or above inclusive of minor injury and illness. It is desirable that applicants have undertaken the non-medical prescribing course.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you feel you have these attributes and a passion to join our team to providing excellent care to our patients then we would like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal enquires and socially distanced facilitated site visits are encouraged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Enquiries and further discussions can be arranged as follows:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Daniel White, Matron, Emergency Department, Urgent Care &lt;strong&gt;daniel.white@tgh.nhs.uk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Samantha Ledwith, Directorate Manager Urgent Care &lt;strong&gt;samantha.ledwith@tgh.nhs.uk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
